article.headline: Illinois St. 90, SE Missouri 71
article.story: NORMAL, Ill. (AP) -- Sophomore Osiris Eldridge scored 27 points and Anthony Slack had 15 points and 13 rebounds to lead Illinois State to a 90-71 victory over Southeast Missouri State on Wednesday in the first round of the Chicago Invitational Challenge. Brandon Holtz added 15 points on five 3-point shots and Emmanuel Holloway came off the bench to score 10 points for Illinois State (2-0). Southeast Missouri State (0-2) led 46-44 at the half, but Illinois State pulled away in the second period on an 18-2 run. Will Bogan led Southeast Missouri State with 23 points. Brandon Foust added 11 points and Calvin Williams had 10 for the Redhawks. Illinois State's 90 points were the most by a Redbird team since February 2001. The Redbirds are 6-1 all-time against Southeast Missouri State, including five straight wins.
